===Etymology===
Eponym, [[w: Donatus Magnus]] + [[-ism]]
===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

#{{Christianity}} An early [[heresy]] which maintained [[apostate]] priests were incapable of administering the [[sacrament]]s, in distinction to the (still-current) orthodox view that any sacrament administered by a properly ordained priest or bishop is valid, no matter how sinful he is, no matter even if he has converted to another religion.


